snippet.textDisplay:
I could not wait to see HBO’s Westworld. I LOVED the original movie concept, fun then deadly. First one to have the concept of a programming virus, and technology trapping the controllers to suffocating because of an electronic door, helpless to watch the guest massacre.

Then Crichton chopped scenes from the film like a guest screaming while on the rack “I have credit cards, a gold American Express”

Future world was AWEFUL in my opinion. Bad Bad FX, boring, a waste of Yule Brenner in a dream sequence, and a horrible showdown between Blythe D. And her robot double.

I LOVED THE FIRST SEASON OF W.W. HBO.

It kept the original idea but created sinister layers.

Season two was not much fun and repetitive and boring.

The latest preview of season 3. Yet another joyless overused dystopian landscape plot.

This is just opinion, I apologize if I offend anyone.

M.E. Boston
